# program.md — improving-skills run goals

Copy this file to `runs/<run-id>/program.md` and edit it before starting
the loop. This file is the agent's north star for what to optimize.

## Target

Path to the SKILL.md being improved:
```
runs/<run-id>/skill/SKILL.md
```

## Goals

Pick one to three goals. Fewer is better — focused runs converge faster.

- [ ] **Tighten triggers.** Reduce false fires on negative prompts while
      keeping all positive prompts firing.
- [ ] **Shrink body.** Reduce token count by ≥30% without losing
      instruction quality.
- [ ] **Sharpen instructions.** Improve LLM-as-judge quality scores on the
      positive prompts; trigger accuracy must not regress.
- [ ] **Promote progressive disclosure.** Move detail out of SKILL.md into
      supporting files (kept one level deep).

## Constraints

These are non-negotiable. Every kept iteration must satisfy them.

- Do not rename or remove frontmatter fields (`name`, `description`,
  `disable-model-invocation`, etc).
- Do not change the skill's `name` value (would break invocation).
- Every kept iteration must pass `eval/check-skill.sh` cleanly.
- Do not delete files referenced from SKILL.md without also removing the
  reference.

## Notes for the agent

Free-form. Anything the agent should know that isn't captured above —
context about the skill's intended user, terms to prefer/avoid, examples
of what "better" looks like.

If the target's `references/learnings.md` has a "Retro log", paste its
`Status: open` entries here as a candidate-edit backlog — real-run
observations the author flagged. They are candidates to try first, not
mandates: each must still pass the harness and raise the composite to survive.

```
<your notes>

### Candidate edits from references/learnings.md retro log (open)
<paste open entries, or "none">
```
